Function Reference/the taxonomies « WordPress Codex
-----------

This template tag can be used within The Loop to display Links for
[taxonomies](/Custom_Taxonomies "Custom Taxonomies") and belonging Terms
for a post without specifying the Post ID. You can also use it outside
The Loop to display the taxonomies for a specific post.

Usage
-----

`  <?php the_taxonomies( $args ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `post` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The post ID to get taxonomies of.
    Default: 0

 `before` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Display before taxonomies list.
    Default: *None*

 `sep` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optiona*) Separate every taxonomy with value in this.
    Default: 'and' (in your language)

 `after` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Display this after the taxonomies list.
    Default: *None*

 `template` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Template used to display the taxonomies list.
    Default: *None*

Returns
-------

A List of Links to your Tags in the taxonomies

Taxonomy Name: \<a
href='[http://yourdomain.com/Term\_Slug/'](http://yourdomain.com/Term_Slug/' "http://yourdomain.com/Term_Slug/'")\>Term
Name/a\>.

\

Example
-------

`  <?php the_taxonomies('before=<ul>&after=</ul>'); ?> `

Source File
-----------

`the_taxonomies()` is located in `wp-includes/taxonomy.php`.

